  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-noncannulated-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk 3. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted based on literature-supported insensitivity of titanium pedicle screw constructs to quasi-static load rate variation and the conservative nature of the single test condition employed. All three QoIs satisfy both quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for the intended regulatory submission use. Supporting project requirements documentation (PRJ-REQ-0041 through PRJ-REQ-0047) confirms alignment with design input requirements, though structured bindsRequirement linkage is deferred to the full profile submission package.",
